WEBVTT

00:04.091 --> 00:04.308
.

00:04.352 --> 00:06.049
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:06.093 --> 00:07.355
sexually based offenses

00:07.398 --> 00:09.661
are considered
especially heinous.

00:09.705 --> 00:12.229
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:12.273 --> 00:14.014
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:14.057 --> 00:15.493
are members of an elite squad

00:15.537 --> 00:17.365
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:17.408 --> 00:19.193
These are their stories.

00:20.324 --> 00:23.501
[light music]

00:23.545 --> 00:26.983
♪

00:27.027 --> 00:28.419
- Wow.

00:28.463 --> 00:31.857
This is a blast from the past.

00:31.901 --> 00:33.163
Where did you find this?

00:33.207 --> 00:34.251
- The cloud.

00:34.295 --> 00:36.210
It's for a class project.

00:36.253 --> 00:37.820
"Where it began,
where it is now."

00:37.863 --> 00:39.126
- Mm.

00:39.169 --> 00:40.605
- I can't believe
you said I was good.

00:40.649 --> 00:43.086
- You were good.

00:43.130 --> 00:45.523
You know, I think there's
an even older one.

00:45.567 --> 00:46.350
- It's okay.

00:46.394 --> 00:48.744
We gotta go anyway.

00:50.311 --> 00:51.964
- You wanna tell me
what's going on?

00:52.008 --> 00:55.011
- It's a surprise
for Mother's Day.

00:55.055 --> 01:00.538
♪

01:00.582 --> 01:04.151
- That's me, Mommy, and Daddy.

01:04.194 --> 01:06.762
- Well, that's a nice
Mother's Day card.

01:06.805 --> 01:10.766
And is that your sister,
Elizabeth, by herself?

01:10.809 --> 01:12.202
I thought you liked her.

01:12.246 --> 01:15.858
- I do, but Beth is away.

01:15.901 --> 01:18.078
It's been a really long time.

01:18.121 --> 01:21.081
Since last Sunday.

01:21.124 --> 01:23.170
- Away? Where'd she go?

01:23.213 --> 01:25.215
- Someplace far.

01:25.259 --> 01:26.782
With Luke.

01:26.825 --> 01:28.131
- Luke?

01:28.175 --> 01:30.916
Is he a relative?

01:30.960 --> 01:33.571
- No, but he's a grown-up.

01:33.615 --> 01:36.183
Mommy and Daddy said
she's fine,

01:36.226 --> 01:40.100
but I don't think
she's ever coming back.

01:40.143 --> 01:43.842
♪

01:43.886 --> 01:45.279
- The principal
called her parents,

01:45.322 --> 01:47.585
but they insisted
she was in bed with the flu.

01:47.629 --> 01:50.371
- But her little brother said
that she was gone.

01:50.414 --> 01:52.329
- Yeah, since last weekend.

01:52.373 --> 01:55.115
He said she left with a man
named Luke.

01:55.158 --> 01:56.768
- Who's Luke?
- The parents say

01:56.812 --> 02:00.250
it's Elijah's imaginary friend,
but he's not that kind of kid.

02:00.294 --> 02:02.513
Something's off.

02:05.299 --> 02:06.474
- Oh, my goodness.

02:06.517 --> 02:09.607
This is all
a complete misunderstanding.

02:09.651 --> 02:13.611
Beth and, um, Luke Davis--
he's a trusted family friend--

02:13.655 --> 02:16.788
they are on a mission trip
upstate rebuilding houses

02:16.832 --> 02:17.833
for refugees.

02:17.876 --> 02:19.878
- And that's her there?

02:19.922 --> 02:21.184
- Yeah.
- Yes.

02:21.228 --> 02:24.492
- So why tell the school
that she was sick

02:24.535 --> 02:28.626
and that Luke was your son's
imaginary friend?

02:28.670 --> 02:29.801
- We should've just
told the truth.

02:29.845 --> 02:31.803
- Yeah.
- But, uh, we didn't want her

02:31.847 --> 02:34.893
to be judged for missing class
for a church project, so.

02:34.937 --> 02:36.852
- So where are they exactly
right now?

02:36.895 --> 02:38.070
- In Bloomingburg.

02:38.114 --> 02:39.768
Our church runs a housing
mission up there.

02:39.811 --> 02:41.335
- Yeah,
Beth really wanted to go,

02:41.378 --> 02:44.599
and Paul and I had work,
so Luke was generous enough

02:44.642 --> 02:46.209
to rent a car and drive her up.

02:46.253 --> 02:47.558
They're staying at the mission

02:47.602 --> 02:49.734
with all of the other kids
and the chaperones.

02:49.778 --> 02:51.997
- When's the last time
you heard from Beth?

02:52.041 --> 02:54.391
- Well, uh, we don't let
her have a cell phone.

02:54.435 --> 02:56.480
- Yeah.
- Um, but, um, Luke did text us

02:56.524 --> 02:58.613
a picture the Sunday
that they left.

02:58.656 --> 02:59.918
- Yeah.
- And--and yeah.

02:59.962 --> 03:01.746
He did say that cell service
would be spotty

03:01.790 --> 03:03.226
once they got up to the woods.

03:03.270 --> 03:05.968
- Well, even so,
we'll need his number.

03:06.011 --> 03:07.056
- Okay.
- Yeah.

03:07.099 --> 03:09.624
- The school made
a police report

03:09.667 --> 03:12.279
so we are gonna have to verify
your daughter's safety.

03:12.322 --> 03:13.367
- Oh.
[both laugh]

03:13.410 --> 03:15.020
- Okay, well, uh,

03:15.064 --> 03:16.674
I have a number
for the head of the mission,

03:16.718 --> 03:18.633
but he doesn't always pick up,
so--

03:18.676 --> 03:21.723
- There's really nothing
to worry about.

03:21.766 --> 03:23.899
She's gonna be back
by Mother's Day.

03:23.942 --> 03:25.117
- Yeah.

03:25.161 --> 03:26.902
[suspenseful music]

03:26.945 --> 03:28.338
- So we cannot verify

03:28.382 --> 03:29.687
that this girl
is at the mission.

03:29.731 --> 03:31.646
- No.
- Do we know that it exists?

03:31.689 --> 03:33.038
- Well, according
to the county sheriff,

03:33.082 --> 03:34.910
it does, and the number
that the parents gave us

03:34.953 --> 03:36.390
for the guy who runs
the mission is legit,

03:36.433 --> 03:38.218
but his mailbox is full.

03:38.261 --> 03:39.349
- Thank you.

03:39.393 --> 03:41.351
We got a bigger problem.

03:41.395 --> 03:43.701
The number for Luke Davis
is a recent burner.

03:43.745 --> 03:44.833
It's turned off.

03:44.876 --> 03:47.052
It's gone off straight
to voicemail.

03:47.096 --> 03:48.880
- I'll alert the state police.

03:48.924 --> 03:50.491
Drive up to Bloomingburg.

03:50.534 --> 03:51.666
Find this girl.

03:56.975 --> 03:59.326
- I told the trooper,
my mailbox is full

03:59.369 --> 04:01.502
because I hate to delete
people's nice messages

04:01.545 --> 04:03.243
and the service up here--
- Yeah, I know. It's spotty.

04:03.286 --> 04:04.287
We just need to know

04:04.331 --> 04:05.810
if you've seen this girl,
Beth Lee.

04:05.854 --> 04:08.378
She would've been with a man
named Luke Davis.

04:08.422 --> 04:09.945
Yeah, he's a worship leader
in the city.

04:09.988 --> 04:11.555
Comes up here every year
with a bunch of kids.

04:11.599 --> 04:12.730
He's great with them.

04:12.774 --> 04:14.079
- Was he and Beth here
this past week?

04:14.123 --> 04:15.516
- No.

04:15.559 --> 04:18.562
Luke called to set it up,
but like I told the trooper,

04:18.606 --> 04:19.650
they never made it up here.

04:19.694 --> 04:20.651
I thought it might be COVID.

04:20.695 --> 04:23.567
- Maybe you should call him.

04:23.611 --> 04:24.960
If you hear from him,
let us know.

04:28.529 --> 04:30.095
- What are we looking at here?

04:30.139 --> 04:31.445
- Nothing good.

04:31.488 --> 04:35.362
♪

04:35.405 --> 04:38.365
[dramatic music]

04:38.408 --> 04:45.546
♪

05:21.712 --> 05:24.106
- Oh, my God.
Something must've happened.

05:24.149 --> 05:26.369
A car accident or--
- Well, we've actually checked

05:26.413 --> 05:27.936
with local authorities
and hospitals,

05:27.979 --> 05:30.286
and no one matching
your daughter's description

05:30.330 --> 05:31.374
has shown up.

05:31.418 --> 05:33.028
- You said he left
in a rental car.

05:33.071 --> 05:34.290
Do you know what agency?

05:34.334 --> 05:35.335
- Um--
- No.

05:35.378 --> 05:36.292
Um, I will--
- Yeah.

05:36.336 --> 05:37.815
- Text Luke again.

05:37.859 --> 05:39.687
- Mrs. Lee,
the number you gave us

05:39.730 --> 05:42.385
came from a burner cell,
a throwaway.

05:42.429 --> 05:44.039
- Uh, Luke said his old phone
wasn't working--

05:44.082 --> 05:44.996
that he had to get a new one.

05:45.040 --> 05:46.128
- From our experience,

05:46.171 --> 05:47.608
people that use burner cells

05:47.651 --> 05:49.436
usually have something to hide.

05:49.479 --> 05:51.394
- Maybe--maybe
they got carjacked.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.614
Luke is always so trusting.
- I know.

05:53.657 --> 05:54.615
- You hear about--
- Why didn't he text you then?

05:54.658 --> 05:55.790
- I don't know! I don't know.

05:55.833 --> 05:57.444
Maybe he's dead
in a ditch somewhere.

05:57.487 --> 05:58.923
- Where's Beth though?

05:58.967 --> 06:00.664
- You said that your daughter
doesn't have a phone,

06:00.708 --> 06:03.711
but does she have, um,
a laptop or an iPad?

06:03.754 --> 06:05.365
- Just for homework,
not social media.

06:05.408 --> 06:07.715
- Still,
any detail might be helpful.

06:07.758 --> 06:11.327
So Mr. Lee, would you mind
Sergeant Tutuola her bedroom?

06:11.371 --> 06:13.634
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

06:14.896 --> 06:17.942
- She goes to school.
She goes to church.

06:17.986 --> 06:18.987
She's a good girl.

06:19.030 --> 06:20.336
It's, uh, right here.

06:20.380 --> 06:23.165
- I can see that.
How'd you meet Luke?

06:23.208 --> 06:24.340
- Uh, through our church.

06:24.384 --> 06:25.646
He's part of our Life Group,

06:25.689 --> 06:27.387
the Bible study we host.

06:27.430 --> 06:28.823
- Is that where he met Beth?

06:28.866 --> 06:33.088
- Yes, and, uh,
he also teaches her guitar.

06:33.131 --> 06:36.613
He's a songwriter--
how he makes a living.

06:36.657 --> 06:39.877
Listen, we always felt
like we could trust him.

06:39.921 --> 06:41.879
- Even so.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.968
Fathers worry.

06:44.012 --> 06:46.449
Upstate for over a week.

06:46.493 --> 06:48.364
That's a lot of time.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.453
[suspenseful music]

06:50.497 --> 06:52.455
- Beth felt called to go.

06:52.499 --> 06:53.717
Claire said yes.

06:53.761 --> 06:57.112
I have been Zooming for work
ten hours a day.

06:58.809 --> 07:00.942
I wasn't paying
enough attention.

07:02.944 --> 07:04.685
[sighs]

07:04.728 --> 07:07.862
Oh, God. What did we do?

07:07.905 --> 07:09.690
- Luke'll text me back.
He always does.

07:09.733 --> 07:11.779
- What can you tell me
about him?

07:11.822 --> 07:13.607
- Uh, ooh.

07:13.650 --> 07:15.086
I've told you everything.

07:15.130 --> 07:17.480
Uh, he's a godly man.

07:17.524 --> 07:19.047
He loves our family.

07:19.090 --> 07:22.920
- Well, do you have an address
or you have his email?

07:22.964 --> 07:24.400
- Uh, no.

07:24.444 --> 07:25.836
But he lives
in the neighborhood.

07:25.880 --> 07:27.925
I think.
I haven't actually been

07:27.969 --> 07:30.145
to his apartment.

07:30.188 --> 07:31.712
- Okay. How 'bout a photo?

07:31.755 --> 07:33.104
- Oh, he's camera-shy.

07:33.148 --> 07:34.541
Always the one taking
the pictures.

07:34.584 --> 07:37.761
You know what,
I might have something

07:37.805 --> 07:41.504
from Beth's birthday party
at Brooklyn Bridge Park.

07:41.548 --> 07:44.202
He didn't know I was recording.
[laughs]

07:44.246 --> 07:45.552
- That would be helpful.

07:45.595 --> 07:48.032
♪

07:48.076 --> 07:50.165
- Black and sweet.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.514
And Benson said
to tell you thank you

07:51.558 --> 07:52.907
for coming in so late.

07:52.950 --> 07:54.735
- Downside of our captains
getting along,

07:54.778 --> 07:57.564
they move us around
like chess pieces.

07:57.607 --> 07:59.435
- What've you got?

07:59.479 --> 08:01.089
- 27 Luke Davises in New York

08:01.132 --> 08:03.439
whose birth dates put them
between 30 and 50.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.485
No cell, address?

08:05.528 --> 08:06.877
- No, he knows how
to stay off the grid.

08:06.921 --> 08:08.749
Benson and Fin
are with the parents now.

08:08.792 --> 08:11.229
- They just let some guy take
their 14-year-old away

08:11.273 --> 08:12.796
for a week?
- Yeah.

08:12.840 --> 08:15.495
- Wouldn't happen in my family.
[phone chimes]

08:17.497 --> 08:19.194
- Benson just sent this.

08:21.718 --> 08:23.415
- And then you'll go back
to G.

08:23.459 --> 08:25.200
- Yeah?
- That's great.

08:25.243 --> 08:26.462
- [laughs]

08:26.506 --> 08:27.811
[indistinct talking]

08:27.855 --> 08:29.247
Like that?
- Make sure you hold tighter.

08:29.291 --> 08:30.205
[soft guitar music]

08:30.248 --> 08:31.946
That's good.

08:31.989 --> 08:34.426
- Yeah, he didn't find Jesus.

08:34.470 --> 08:36.037
He found Beth.

08:36.080 --> 08:37.386
- And then you'll go back
to G.

08:37.429 --> 08:38.996
- Okay.

08:41.608 --> 08:43.479
- Come this Sunday
to Two Echoes Church.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.785
We'll sing and pray together

08:44.828 --> 08:46.569
and celebrate the word
of the Lord.

08:46.613 --> 08:48.005
- Nice, babe.

08:48.049 --> 08:49.180
- Pastor Adams?

08:49.224 --> 08:50.573
- Can we help you?

08:50.617 --> 08:51.792
- Yeah. NYPD.

08:51.835 --> 08:52.880
We've been talking to the Lees

08:52.923 --> 08:54.359
about their missing daughter.

08:54.403 --> 08:55.665
- Oh, yes. They called us.

08:55.709 --> 08:57.275
But I'm sure
Beth's not missing.

08:57.319 --> 08:59.887
She's with Luke. He texted us.
Everything's fine.

08:59.930 --> 09:02.324
- Okay, but we haven't been
able to reach either of them.

09:02.367 --> 09:03.804
- Well, I know they're not
at the mission,

09:03.847 --> 09:06.328
but Luke's taken church kids
up there lots of times.

09:06.371 --> 09:08.156
He probably just found
another house to work on.

09:08.199 --> 09:10.550
- How long have you two
known Luke?

09:10.593 --> 09:12.943
- He joined our ministry
three years ago?

09:12.987 --> 09:14.815
He's very active
with the teenage members

09:14.858 --> 09:16.207
in the music program.

09:16.251 --> 09:17.861
- Do you know anything
about his background?

09:17.905 --> 09:19.646
As we said, we're having
trouble locating him.

09:19.689 --> 09:21.865
There are a lot of Luke Davises
in New York.

09:21.909 --> 09:24.825
- Okay, but you really
don't have to worry.

09:24.868 --> 09:26.740
We did
a thorough background check.

09:26.783 --> 09:28.568
Anyone who works with kids...

09:31.875 --> 09:34.835
- Yeah, I know we promised
confidentiality, Daniel,

09:34.878 --> 09:37.228
but these are cops,
and they sound serious.

09:37.272 --> 09:40.754
I think we should tell them.
- Tell us what?

09:40.797 --> 09:42.625
- I don't understand.
Who's Nick Pearce?

09:42.669 --> 09:44.801
- The man that you've known
as Luke Davis.

09:44.845 --> 09:46.629
- Pearce is the son

09:46.673 --> 09:48.065
of a wealthy family
in Rhode Island,

09:48.109 --> 09:50.677
and they told us through
their attorneys,

09:50.720 --> 09:52.635
they have no idea where he is.

09:52.679 --> 09:54.768
No cell phone, no credit card,
no bank account.

09:54.811 --> 09:55.856
Nothing to track him.

09:55.899 --> 09:57.161
- No, but this--
[laughs]

09:57.205 --> 09:58.641
This is not possible.

09:58.685 --> 10:03.211
- This man is not
who he told you that he was,

10:03.254 --> 10:05.387
and he didn't take
your daughter where he told you

10:05.430 --> 10:07.519
he was going to take her.

10:07.563 --> 10:08.869
Mrs. Lee...

10:10.435 --> 10:13.830
We believe that your daughter
has been kidnapped.

10:13.874 --> 10:17.442
[tense music]

10:17.486 --> 10:19.140
- Son of a bitch.

10:20.794 --> 10:23.927
I'm sorry.
- You're entitled, Mr. Lee.

10:23.971 --> 10:26.016
- As far as we can tell,
Nick's been using the alias

10:26.060 --> 10:28.932
Luke Davis since he met Beth
in 2019.

10:28.976 --> 10:31.674
- Where is he?
Where's my daughter?

10:31.718 --> 10:33.328
- We're trying to find them.

10:33.371 --> 10:35.983
Pearce has been renting
an apartment in Gramercy.

10:36.026 --> 10:37.898
Police are tearing
that apart now.

10:37.941 --> 10:41.553
We're also checking
the rental car agencies.

10:41.597 --> 10:43.904
- He took my daughter.

10:43.947 --> 10:44.861
Why?

10:44.905 --> 10:49.039
- Daniel and Molly told us

10:49.083 --> 10:50.650
that he was a good person.

10:50.693 --> 10:53.130
They told us that it--that--

10:53.174 --> 10:55.045
- Because he manipulated them
too.

10:55.089 --> 10:56.873
Nick told them
when he joined the church

10:56.917 --> 10:59.528
that he was impressed
by some young teens

10:59.571 --> 11:00.747
he had seen praying together

11:00.790 --> 11:02.444
in a youth group,
including Beth.

11:02.487 --> 11:06.448
- Yes, he confided in me
that he envied the kids

11:06.491 --> 11:10.365
at our church, that his home
lacked a spiritual center.

11:10.408 --> 11:11.714
- Mrs. Lee.

11:11.758 --> 11:15.457
Claire, I need you to listen
to me now.

11:15.500 --> 11:19.330
This man joined your church,

11:19.374 --> 11:21.637
and he changed his name,

11:21.681 --> 11:23.944
and he befriended your family

11:23.987 --> 11:25.946
because he was targeting Beth

11:25.989 --> 11:27.904
from the moment
that he saw her.

11:27.948 --> 11:29.210
- That isn't true. He wasn't.

11:29.253 --> 11:30.690
- I know this is hard to--
- No.

11:30.733 --> 11:32.909
You do not understand.

11:32.953 --> 11:36.608
He was targeting me.

11:36.652 --> 11:39.263
[dark music]

11:39.307 --> 11:41.048
Paul can never know.

11:44.007 --> 11:46.488
Luke and I are very much
in love.

11:46.531 --> 11:52.407
♪

11:56.150 --> 11:56.367
.

11:56.411 --> 11:58.195
- Claire Lee and Nick Pearce
were having an affair

11:58.239 --> 11:58.979
for over a year?

11:59.022 --> 12:00.458
- Playing the long game.

12:00.502 --> 12:02.373
Seducing the mother to get
to the daughter,

12:02.417 --> 12:05.072
but I don't think
that the parents are complicit.

12:05.115 --> 12:07.030
- Where are the Lees now?

12:07.074 --> 12:09.380
- Home. Claire is telling Paul.

12:09.424 --> 12:11.208
- Well, what about Nick
and Beth's relationship?

12:11.252 --> 12:12.470
- Oh, we scoured her computer.

12:12.514 --> 12:14.342
Mostly they exchanged
Bible verses.

12:14.385 --> 12:16.170
A lot of Paul
to the Thessalonians.

12:16.213 --> 12:17.562
- Oh, so love letters.
So he's grooming her.

12:17.606 --> 12:19.956
- Pearce rented a car from JFK
a week ago.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.828
Troopers found it
in an overnight lot

12:21.871 --> 12:22.959
in Middletown.

12:23.003 --> 12:24.395
Key was in the drop box.

12:24.439 --> 12:26.049
- So he hasn't used
the credit card

12:26.093 --> 12:27.529
since he rented the car.

12:27.572 --> 12:29.923
So maybe they're on foot,
hitchhiking.

12:29.966 --> 12:32.186
- Here it is.
PurposeMusic, LLC

12:32.229 --> 12:33.970
in Rhode Island.

12:34.014 --> 12:35.667
- Meaning?
- Well, Claire told us

12:35.711 --> 12:38.322
that Nick had Venmoed her money
from an old business account,

12:38.366 --> 12:41.282
so maybe he Venmoed
somebody else.

12:41.325 --> 12:42.979
- I'm looking,
but his account's private.

12:43.023 --> 12:44.459
- I'll get a subpoena.

12:44.502 --> 12:45.416
- Thanks.

12:49.943 --> 12:51.379
- How did you find me?

12:51.422 --> 12:53.424
I haven't talked to Nick Pearce
in years.

12:53.468 --> 12:55.296
- Through his old LLC.

12:55.339 --> 12:59.256
He Venmoed you about $5,000
three years ago.

12:59.300 --> 13:00.388
May I ask why?

13:00.431 --> 13:02.216
- Uh, we were dating.

13:02.259 --> 13:04.305
I lost my job.

13:04.348 --> 13:05.785
He offered to help me buy a car

13:05.828 --> 13:07.917
so my daughter didn't have
to take the bus to school.

13:07.961 --> 13:09.571
I should have declared it.

13:09.614 --> 13:11.878
- We don't care about that.
We're just trying to find Nick.

13:11.921 --> 13:13.227
Do you've a contact number?

13:13.270 --> 13:15.229
- No. What's he done?

13:15.272 --> 13:18.623
- He may be involved
in an abduction.

13:20.277 --> 13:22.540
- Lemme guess. A young girl?

13:22.584 --> 13:24.151
- Why, something happen
to your daughter?

13:24.194 --> 13:27.023
[tense music]

13:27.067 --> 13:29.286
- Eva was 12.

13:29.330 --> 13:30.940
The three of us,
we were gonna spend the summer

13:30.984 --> 13:33.595
at Nick's lake cabin upstate.

13:33.638 --> 13:35.205
But then my ex bumped on that.

13:35.249 --> 13:38.339
He insisted Eva spend
the summer with him.

13:38.382 --> 13:42.299
The next day, Nick dumped me.

13:42.343 --> 13:43.910
I guess
I wasn't the one he wanted

13:43.953 --> 13:45.346
to spend the summer with.

13:45.389 --> 13:48.871
- Okay, did Nick ever
spend time alone with Eva?

13:48.915 --> 13:51.526
- I used to work
the night shift.

13:51.569 --> 13:54.094
But she swore to me
that they just

13:54.137 --> 13:55.660
watched movies and cuddled.

13:55.704 --> 13:58.794
- But you were worried
about it?

13:58.838 --> 14:01.231
- I could never say a bad word
about him.

14:01.275 --> 14:02.885
It was like he brainwashed her.

14:02.929 --> 14:05.192
- Right, and this lake house,
do you remember where it was?

14:05.235 --> 14:07.455
- He showed us pictures. A map.

14:07.498 --> 14:10.197
The town, the cabin.

14:10.240 --> 14:11.720
It was pretty remote.

14:11.763 --> 14:14.810
- Okay.
- Near Tupper Lake.

14:14.854 --> 14:18.901
I remember
it was off Gentle Rain Drive.

14:18.945 --> 14:22.862
- The most powerful act of love
is forgiveness.

14:22.905 --> 14:25.647
I am working on that.
- Oh, good.

14:25.690 --> 14:27.997
Because your daughter
is gonna need both of you.

14:28.041 --> 14:29.912
- You found her?
- We're close.

14:29.956 --> 14:33.829
Nick's family has a cabin
on Tupper Lake upstate.

14:33.873 --> 14:38.312
Has he ever mentioned taking
Beth or your family there?

14:38.355 --> 14:39.966
- Mm-mm.
- Uh, no.

14:40.009 --> 14:42.185
But apparently there's a lot
of things he didn't mention.

14:42.229 --> 14:43.447
- Paul,
this is about our daughter.

14:43.491 --> 14:45.623
- Mr. and Mrs. Lee,

14:45.667 --> 14:47.843
this man has been grooming
your daughter

14:47.887 --> 14:49.845
for over 2 1/2 years.

14:49.889 --> 14:53.022
And now he's been alone
with her for over a week,

14:53.066 --> 14:56.852
and in my experience,
there are many different ways

14:56.896 --> 14:59.942
that a teenage girl could react
to a situation like this.

14:59.986 --> 15:03.293
- I--I am sure
he wouldn't hurt her.

15:03.337 --> 15:05.687
- We understand, Captain.

15:05.730 --> 15:09.256
Just, uh,
bring our daughter home.

15:09.299 --> 15:12.259
[tense music]

15:12.302 --> 15:19.396
♪

15:40.156 --> 15:41.201
- NYPD!

15:41.244 --> 15:46.771
♪

15:46.815 --> 15:48.991
- Who are you?
- Beth, we're the police, okay?

15:49.035 --> 15:50.558
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.
- Nick Pearce!

15:50.601 --> 15:52.038
- What's going on?
- You have the wrong man.

15:52.081 --> 15:53.387
- His name's Luke, not Nick.

15:53.430 --> 15:55.737
- Get your hands up!
- Don't hurt him. Please.

15:55.780 --> 15:57.565
- We're not gonna hurt anybody,
okay?

15:57.608 --> 15:58.740
- Call her parents.

15:58.783 --> 16:00.263
They know she's safe here,
okay?

16:00.307 --> 16:02.091
- Nick Pearce,
you're under arrest

16:02.135 --> 16:03.701
for kidnapping a minor.

16:03.745 --> 16:06.748
- This is the devil in action.
Don't be afraid.

16:06.791 --> 16:07.967
- Beth, it's time to come home,
okay?

16:08.010 --> 16:09.272
- I am home.

16:09.316 --> 16:11.405
- You need to come with us.
- No.

16:11.448 --> 16:13.059
- Honey. Come--come with me.
- No. No.

16:13.102 --> 16:14.408
- Come on, come on.
- No! No!

16:14.451 --> 16:15.322
- You have the right
to remain silent.

16:15.365 --> 16:16.888
- Beth, stay strong.

16:16.932 --> 16:18.194
The scriptures say
we'll be tested.

16:18.238 --> 16:19.935
- Test this:
anything you say

16:19.979 --> 16:22.155
can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

16:22.198 --> 16:23.591
- Beth.
- What are you doing?

16:23.634 --> 16:25.288
He didn't kidnap me.

16:25.332 --> 16:26.507
This is God's will.

16:26.550 --> 16:30.641
♪

16:34.210 --> 16:34.384
.

16:34.428 --> 16:35.820
- Hey. How's Beth doing?

16:35.864 --> 16:37.692
- She's lucid. Calm.

16:37.735 --> 16:38.954
Nothing on the tox screen.

16:38.998 --> 16:41.652
She's dehydrated, bug bites,
but otherwise

16:41.696 --> 16:42.697
not physically harmed.

16:42.740 --> 16:43.872
- Sexual assault?

16:43.915 --> 16:44.829
- Talked to her
in the ambulance.

16:44.873 --> 16:45.830
She said all they did was hug,

16:45.874 --> 16:47.484
but she sounded coached.

16:47.528 --> 16:50.574
- Did you do a rape kit?
- We asked. She refused.

16:50.618 --> 16:52.620
She also refused
a pregnancy test.

16:52.663 --> 16:53.751
- She's 14.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.884
I mean,
it's her right to decide.

16:55.927 --> 16:58.104
- Her, uh, parents disagree.

16:58.147 --> 17:01.194
I explained that to force her
is against hospital policy

17:01.237 --> 17:02.586
and the law.

17:02.630 --> 17:05.111
Good luck talking to them.

17:05.154 --> 17:07.504
- Mr. and Mrs. Lee,
so the good news

17:07.548 --> 17:10.159
is that your daughter is safe
and not physically harmed.

17:10.203 --> 17:11.595
- And we are very grateful.

17:11.639 --> 17:14.381
- She said that Luke--Nick
didn't do anything to her

17:14.424 --> 17:15.425
like that.

17:15.469 --> 17:17.079
- She's been brainwashed,
Claire.

17:17.123 --> 17:19.560
- She was reluctant
to leave the cabin.

17:19.603 --> 17:22.084
And him. She's attached.

17:22.128 --> 17:23.868
- Well, they've been close
for a long time.

17:23.912 --> 17:25.566
That doesn't mean
that they had sex.

17:25.609 --> 17:28.090
Did--did she say that they did?

17:28.134 --> 17:30.092
- Uh, she said
that they hugged.

17:30.136 --> 17:32.921
- Right, which is why we need
that rape kit, right?

17:32.964 --> 17:34.401
To prove that nothing happened.

17:34.444 --> 17:37.882
- She's 14, and you understand
that we cannot force her

17:37.926 --> 17:39.362
to consent to an exam.

17:39.406 --> 17:41.234
- Why?
I'm her mother. She's my child.

17:41.277 --> 17:43.410
I--I force her
to eat her vegetables

17:43.453 --> 17:44.585
and do her homework.

17:44.628 --> 17:46.978
Why can't you sedate her
and just do it?

17:47.022 --> 17:49.242
- That's not an option
in New York.

17:49.285 --> 17:51.113
- [sighs]
- Okay, Claire.

17:51.157 --> 17:53.420
Now's not the time
to force her to do anything.

17:53.463 --> 17:55.596
Maybe a test for disease
or pregnancy.

17:55.639 --> 17:58.468
- We cannot force her
to have a pregnancy exam

17:58.512 --> 18:00.166
without her permission.

18:00.209 --> 18:02.255
- She's not pregnant.

18:02.298 --> 18:05.954
Paul, he wouldn't--
- Do you hear yourself?

18:05.997 --> 18:08.304
We're still protecting him.

18:08.348 --> 18:13.092
He kidnapped Beth.
- We don't know that, Paul.

18:13.135 --> 18:15.790
She is safe. They said.

18:15.833 --> 18:20.925
And God's will is unknowable.

18:20.969 --> 18:23.885
[suspenseful music]

18:23.928 --> 18:24.929
♪

18:24.973 --> 18:27.193
- No, I love the Lee family.

18:27.236 --> 18:30.239
I would never do anything
to hurt them or Beth.

18:30.283 --> 18:31.893
- Other than kidnapping her?

18:31.936 --> 18:33.938
- The Lees consented
to my client taking Beth

18:33.982 --> 18:35.810
upstate for faith-based work.

18:35.853 --> 18:37.159
- Yeah, to build houses.

18:37.203 --> 18:39.379
Not to spirit their daughter
away to a cabin

18:39.422 --> 18:41.163
out of cell phone service,
out of contact.

18:41.207 --> 18:43.122
- You know, I love that you use
the word "spirit"

18:43.165 --> 18:45.472
because that's exactly what
this was.

18:45.515 --> 18:47.822
It was a spiritual journey.
It was a vision.

18:47.865 --> 18:49.693
- Nick, lemme do the talking.

18:49.737 --> 18:51.826
- No, no, no. Go on, Nick.

18:51.869 --> 18:53.436
What vision?

18:53.480 --> 18:57.484
- Of Beth and I planting
the seeds of a new church.

18:57.527 --> 19:00.182
Beth and I, we both felt it,
and we knew we were going

19:00.226 --> 19:03.490
to need help,
so I was like, "Okay, God.

19:03.533 --> 19:04.752
Yeah, you're in control."

19:04.795 --> 19:06.580
- And God told you
that this church

19:06.623 --> 19:08.364
had to be planted at a cabin
in the woods?

19:08.408 --> 19:10.018
- Yeah,
in the vision I was there.

19:10.061 --> 19:11.280
I was surrounded

19:11.324 --> 19:13.456
by the God-given beauty
of this place.

19:13.500 --> 19:15.154
And I hadn't been there
since I was a kid.

19:15.197 --> 19:17.330
It's a miracle that it
manifested itself to me.

19:17.373 --> 19:19.810
- It wasn't that much
of a miracle.

19:19.854 --> 19:23.074
Remember your ex-girlfriend
Nadine and her daughter, Eva?

19:23.118 --> 19:24.946
You were gonna take them
to the same cabin.

19:24.989 --> 19:26.556
- Yeah, I didn't.

19:26.600 --> 19:28.863
They clearly were not part
of God's plan.

19:28.906 --> 19:30.604
- Can we get back
to the here and now?

19:30.647 --> 19:34.782
My client did nothing that Beth
or her parents didn't approve.

19:34.825 --> 19:38.873
This girl is safe and unharmed.
There is no crime.

19:38.916 --> 19:40.396
- You may doubt me.

19:40.440 --> 19:45.488
I understand that's going
to happen, but talk to Beth.

19:45.532 --> 19:47.403
She'll give you
the God's honest truth.

19:47.447 --> 19:51.625
♪

19:51.668 --> 19:53.322
- Hey.
- Where's Luke?

19:53.366 --> 19:54.628
I wanna see him.

19:54.671 --> 19:56.760
- That's--that's not possible
right now, Beth.

19:56.804 --> 19:58.197
- Then can I just go home?

19:58.240 --> 19:59.241
- Back to the cabin?

19:59.285 --> 20:01.591
- No. I meant my home.

20:01.635 --> 20:02.940
I miss Elijah.

20:02.984 --> 20:06.292
- I have met Elijah.
He's very sweet.

20:06.335 --> 20:08.381
And he's the one that told us
that you were missing.

20:08.424 --> 20:10.948
- You're trying
to indoctrinate me.

20:10.992 --> 20:13.081
Luke said
that's what nonbelievers do.

20:13.124 --> 20:16.258
- Beth, I'm trying to help you.
- By treating me like a child?

20:16.302 --> 20:17.912
Arresting Luke?
He didn't do anything.

20:17.955 --> 20:21.916
- Well, Detective Rollins
may not see how mature you are

20:21.959 --> 20:26.181
because her daughters
are so young.

20:26.225 --> 20:27.704
- You know, Captain,
you're right.

20:30.838 --> 20:32.753
- So your kids are in college?

20:32.796 --> 20:35.059
- Well, let's talk about you.

20:35.103 --> 20:39.368
I just know
how mature 14 can be

20:39.412 --> 20:43.764
because I was the same way
myself.

20:43.807 --> 20:48.203
And some of the strongest women
in the Bible

20:48.247 --> 20:50.640
were as young as 12, right?

20:50.684 --> 20:53.556
- Esther and Ruth. Mary.

20:53.600 --> 20:55.079
They ran empires.

20:55.123 --> 20:56.646
Got married.
Had children of their own.

20:56.690 --> 20:58.866
- Is that what you wanna do,
Beth?

20:58.909 --> 21:01.129
With Luke?

21:01.172 --> 21:03.218
- I know what you're asking.

21:03.262 --> 21:05.002
Luke and I are still pure.

21:06.003 --> 21:07.875
- Okay.

21:07.918 --> 21:12.532
Okay, but you did just go away
together on vacation.

21:12.575 --> 21:15.186
So...help me understand.

21:15.230 --> 21:17.624
Is that like--is that like
father and daughter?

21:17.667 --> 21:20.148
- No, that's disgusting.

21:20.191 --> 21:21.715
And he's nothing
like my father.

21:21.758 --> 21:25.153
- Okay.
So more like a boyfriend or...?

21:25.196 --> 21:27.068
♪

21:27.111 --> 21:29.070
Or maybe somebody
that you're in love with?

21:30.811 --> 21:33.422
- I do love him.

21:33.466 --> 21:35.119
And he loves me.

21:35.163 --> 21:36.991
Just not like my father.

21:37.034 --> 21:39.515
- Well, I can understand that.
You're--

21:39.559 --> 21:43.563
look, you're old enough
to make decisions like that

21:43.606 --> 21:48.045
about sleeping together
or getting married.

21:48.089 --> 21:51.310
- I--I can't tell you
about that.

21:51.353 --> 21:54.791
- Luke says no one
will understand God's truth.

21:54.835 --> 21:57.925
That we'll be judged.

21:57.968 --> 22:01.320
- Well, I can see how important
this is to you.

22:01.363 --> 22:04.235
And I respect that.

22:04.279 --> 22:05.715
But will you--

22:05.759 --> 22:08.109
will you help me understand?

22:09.763 --> 22:13.680
- His plan was God's plan.

22:13.723 --> 22:17.684
Jesus said,
"I will come again."

22:17.727 --> 22:19.990
And that day has come.

22:20.034 --> 22:23.864
♪

22:23.907 --> 22:25.866
- Nick had a vision.

22:25.909 --> 22:27.520
Well, at least he's consistent.

22:27.563 --> 22:29.522
He's got Beth thinking
that he's the Second Coming.

22:29.565 --> 22:31.262
- Yeah, no rape kit,
no admission of sex?

22:31.306 --> 22:32.873
- Not for lack of trying,
but apparently I'm better

22:32.916 --> 22:34.788
at talking to psychopaths
than teenage girls.

22:34.831 --> 22:36.355
- Okay.
- Huh?

22:36.398 --> 22:38.705
- This guy has gotten so deep
into Beth's head.

22:38.748 --> 22:41.534
So Khaldun,
anything from the cabin?

22:41.577 --> 22:43.057
- No contraceptives or anything

22:43.100 --> 22:44.580
that would indicate
sexual activity.

22:44.624 --> 22:46.713
- We sent the bedding
and the towels to the lab.

22:46.756 --> 22:48.845
Still waiting on bodily fluids
and DNA.

22:48.889 --> 22:51.674
- Which, without a rape kit,
isn't probative anyway.

22:51.718 --> 22:52.936
- Well, this guy was prepped
for the long haul.

22:52.980 --> 22:54.285
He had a least three months'
worth of food

22:54.329 --> 22:55.417
and medical supplies up there.

22:55.461 --> 22:56.723
- Where are the parents
in all this?

22:56.766 --> 22:58.420
Are they on the same page?
- The husband seems

22:58.464 --> 22:59.421
to have a little more clarity.

22:59.465 --> 23:00.553
- And Claire believes

23:00.596 --> 23:02.250
that "Luke" can be redeemed.

23:02.293 --> 23:03.773
- Oh, so she's still in love
with him.

23:03.817 --> 23:04.905
- Yeah.

23:04.948 --> 23:06.428
- This is gonna be a problem
in trial.

23:06.472 --> 23:07.995
- Yeah,
just keep him behind bars.

23:08.038 --> 23:11.694
Even if he can walk on water,
he can't bend steel.

23:11.738 --> 23:13.783
- I'll see what I can do.

23:18.484 --> 23:21.095
- Nick Pearce,
on the charge of kidnapping

23:21.138 --> 23:22.096
in the second degree?

23:22.139 --> 23:23.140
- Not guilty, Your Honor.

23:23.184 --> 23:24.446
- People on bail?
- Remand.

23:24.490 --> 23:26.056
Mr. Pearce is being charged

23:26.100 --> 23:27.101
with abducting
a 14-year-old girl

23:27.144 --> 23:28.276
for over a week.

23:28.319 --> 23:29.756
He's been living
under an assumed identity

23:29.799 --> 23:31.061
for the last 2 1/2 years.

23:31.105 --> 23:32.236
We consider him a flight risk.
- Your Honor,

23:32.280 --> 23:33.368
there was no kidnapping.

23:33.412 --> 23:35.979
My client had permission
from her parents

23:36.023 --> 23:37.546
to accompany Beth upstate.

23:37.590 --> 23:39.113
- Not to a remote cabin
in the woods

23:39.156 --> 23:40.419
with living supplies
for months.

23:40.462 --> 23:42.856
- I request my client be ROR'd,
Your Honor.

23:42.899 --> 23:44.553
He has no record.

23:44.597 --> 23:46.642
He's a well-respected member
of his church.

23:46.686 --> 23:48.122
- A church that he
insinuated himself into...

23:48.165 --> 23:49.297
- Okay. Well, well--

23:49.340 --> 23:50.733
- Just like he did
the Lee family.

23:50.777 --> 23:53.170
- Hold up. Hold up.
My client is the victim here.

23:53.214 --> 23:56.522
The Lees took advantage
of his search for spirituality

23:56.565 --> 23:59.481
to seduce him into a lifestyle
of sexual deviance.

23:59.525 --> 24:01.396
- Oh, Your Honor.
- Be careful, Mr. Pace.

24:01.440 --> 24:02.702
- How can he just say that?
- I'm sorry.

24:02.745 --> 24:04.007
- If anything,
the Lees' household

24:04.051 --> 24:06.140
was endangering the welfare
of a minor, not--

24:06.183 --> 24:07.968
- That is not true!

24:08.011 --> 24:09.883
- Sit down, Mr. Lee. Sit down.

24:09.926 --> 24:11.754
- I also have evidence
that my client is willing

24:11.798 --> 24:15.018
to testify to
that Paul Lee forced him

24:15.062 --> 24:18.761
into demeaning sexual acts
that left my client open

24:18.805 --> 24:19.762
to being blackmailed.

24:19.806 --> 24:20.894
So given all of this,

24:20.937 --> 24:21.982
I'll be bringing in a motion

24:22.025 --> 24:23.766
to drop the charges.

24:23.810 --> 24:26.726
[tense music]

24:26.769 --> 24:29.859
♪

24:32.993 --> 24:33.384
.

24:33.428 --> 24:35.082
- Did the judge believe that?

24:35.125 --> 24:37.084
He--he just let Nick out
on bail.

24:37.127 --> 24:38.825
- Don't worry.
There's an Order of Protection.

24:38.868 --> 24:40.391
- No, no.

24:40.435 --> 24:42.524
His lawyer should be forced
to go and admit

24:42.568 --> 24:43.525
that that was a lie.

24:43.569 --> 24:44.918
- Claire.
- No, what?

24:44.961 --> 24:46.833
- Let's not bring
more attention to this.

24:46.876 --> 24:48.008
- Detective Rollins,
do you think you could

24:48.051 --> 24:49.183
take Claire to get some water?

24:49.226 --> 24:50.184
Maybe a cup of coffee?

24:50.227 --> 24:51.533
- Absolutely, Counselor.

24:54.580 --> 24:56.016
- Mr. Lee.
- Yeah.

24:56.059 --> 24:58.975
- Let's talk in private.

24:59.019 --> 25:00.368
- It's not what you think.

25:00.411 --> 25:02.718
- Nobody's making
any judgements.

25:02.762 --> 25:04.241
- We need to know

25:04.285 --> 25:05.547
if there's anything
Nick might know

25:05.591 --> 25:07.593
that you haven't told us.

25:07.636 --> 25:08.594
- [sighs]

25:11.205 --> 25:12.815
I should've told someone.

25:12.859 --> 25:13.860
- Told someone what?

25:13.903 --> 25:15.688
- [laughs]

25:15.731 --> 25:17.951
I thought he was as ashamed
as I was.

25:19.605 --> 25:22.695
- Why don't you just tell us
what's going on?

25:22.738 --> 25:24.566
- I cannot believe
that lawyer was just allowed

25:24.610 --> 25:25.785
to lie like that in court.

25:25.828 --> 25:27.134
- We don't know
what Nick told him.

25:27.177 --> 25:28.570
- Well, it was clearly a lie.

25:28.614 --> 25:30.006
If anything
like that did happen,

25:30.050 --> 25:31.399
Paul would've told me.

25:31.442 --> 25:32.531
- Well, Claire,
there are things

25:32.574 --> 25:34.533
that you didn't tell Paul.

25:36.622 --> 25:39.233
- [sighs] Well, I--I didn't
want to hurt him.

25:39.276 --> 25:42.323
And Paul and I...

25:44.543 --> 25:48.372
Things changed between us
after Elijah was born.

25:48.416 --> 25:52.725
I was--I was lonely.

25:52.768 --> 25:54.030
- And you and Nick
were together,

25:54.074 --> 25:55.510
so he would've known that.

25:55.554 --> 25:57.686
- Of course,
I told Nick everything and--

25:57.730 --> 26:02.082
he knew that I missed
being intimate with Paul.

26:02.125 --> 26:05.607
- So he knew Paul--Paul and you
hadn't had sex in a while.

26:07.348 --> 26:09.393
- My husband is not gay.

26:09.437 --> 26:10.917
He's not.

26:10.960 --> 26:12.440
[suspenseful music]

26:12.483 --> 26:14.311
- Claire, I'm just trying--
- I'm--I'm--

26:14.355 --> 26:17.445
I need to go pick up Beth
and Elijah.

26:17.488 --> 26:19.099
Thank you for the coffee.

26:19.142 --> 26:22.406
♪

26:22.450 --> 26:25.453
- We were breaking down
the stage...

26:25.496 --> 26:27.934
after a service.

26:27.977 --> 26:29.065
Loading the truck.

26:31.024 --> 26:36.246
I guess, uh, we were both
a little loaded too.

26:36.290 --> 26:37.421
- Okay.

26:37.465 --> 26:39.119
- [sighs]

26:39.162 --> 26:42.513
I don't--I don't usually drink,
but it was Nick's birthday.

26:42.557 --> 26:44.298
He'd gotten some bourbon
and beer to celebrate.

26:44.341 --> 26:45.995
- And it's just the two of you?

26:46.039 --> 26:48.432
- I never got the sense
that he had friends,

26:48.476 --> 26:50.565
so I felt like
I couldn't say no.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.393
- I get that.

26:52.436 --> 26:53.568
What happened?

26:56.310 --> 26:59.400
- We were sitting
in the theater.

26:59.443 --> 27:01.271
Talking about our childhoods.

27:01.315 --> 27:02.882
Drinking.

27:02.925 --> 27:04.535
It got intense.

27:04.579 --> 27:07.930
♪

27:07.974 --> 27:10.237
We hugged.

27:10.280 --> 27:12.761
Then...

27:12.805 --> 27:14.807
he put his hand on my leg.

27:14.850 --> 27:17.679
I didn't--I didn't really think
anything of it.

27:17.723 --> 27:18.854
But...

27:20.726 --> 27:22.902
Then he unzipped my pants.

27:25.774 --> 27:26.862
Uh...

27:28.385 --> 27:29.952
I guess I just...

27:29.996 --> 27:34.914
♪

27:34.957 --> 27:37.481
[inhales deeply]

27:37.525 --> 27:39.092
I guess I just went with it.

27:41.181 --> 27:45.402
'Cause it was easier
than embarrassing him.

27:47.840 --> 27:51.191
- Okay. Then what happened?

27:51.234 --> 27:54.368
- He swore that he wasn't gay.

27:54.411 --> 27:58.589
But that he just, um,
felt close to me.

28:00.722 --> 28:05.379
And we agreed that it was best
not to tell anyone.

28:05.422 --> 28:06.902
It was a sin.

28:08.425 --> 28:09.600
We prayed.

28:12.386 --> 28:13.648
- Just that one time?

28:13.692 --> 28:19.175
♪

28:19.219 --> 28:21.221
- [sighs]

28:21.264 --> 28:22.570
Maybe once or twice after.

28:26.356 --> 28:30.056
Does, uh,
does Claire have to know?

28:32.798 --> 28:34.147
It would just hurt her.

28:34.190 --> 28:36.497
- Paul, she's gonna find out.

28:36.540 --> 28:37.890
In my experience,
anything a defendant

28:37.933 --> 28:40.240
can use against you,
they usually do.

28:40.283 --> 28:43.678
♪

28:43.722 --> 28:46.899
- So this guy made moves
on the mother and the father

28:46.942 --> 28:49.902
as insurance policies in case
he needs to blackmail them?

28:49.945 --> 28:52.513
- He is a sophisticated
predator.

28:52.556 --> 28:54.776
He gained their trust.
He got leverage.

28:54.820 --> 28:57.431
All to be with Beth.
He...

28:57.474 --> 28:58.475
he's obsessed.

28:58.519 --> 29:00.260
- And dangerous.
- Not anymore.

29:00.303 --> 29:02.305
I mean, can't Carisi get
a conviction on kidnapping?

29:02.349 --> 29:05.004
- It's not on Carisi,
and Beth won't testify,

29:05.047 --> 29:07.093
and the parents
did give permission

29:07.136 --> 29:08.007
for Nick to take her.

29:08.050 --> 29:09.791
- This level of manipulation,

29:09.835 --> 29:11.140
he has to have done it before.

29:11.184 --> 29:12.707
Is there no case to be made

29:12.751 --> 29:14.056
with Nadine and the daughter?

29:14.100 --> 29:15.754
- Well, we tried,
and Nadine is willing to help,

29:15.797 --> 29:17.712
but Eva's father is against it.

29:17.756 --> 29:19.366
- She's probably scared
of losing custody

29:19.409 --> 29:21.934
so she won't cooperate.

29:21.977 --> 29:25.372
This guy knows how
to pick his victims.

29:25.415 --> 29:28.462
- "Have I become your enemy
by telling you the truth?"

29:28.505 --> 29:29.811
Book of Galatians.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.595
- What, are you Bible-splaining
to me now?

29:31.639 --> 29:33.206
- No,
I'm just explaining to you

29:33.249 --> 29:36.557
that a lot uncomfortable truths
have emerged.

29:36.600 --> 29:38.124
- You called this meeting.
- Yeah.

29:38.167 --> 29:39.778
Where are we
on dropping the charges?

29:39.821 --> 29:41.649
- Nowhere, your client's still
looking at Kidnapping Two

29:41.692 --> 29:42.650
at a minimum.

29:42.693 --> 29:43.738
- The thing is,

29:43.782 --> 29:44.826
if you put my client on trial,

29:44.870 --> 29:46.262
I'm gonna put the Lees
on trial.

29:46.306 --> 29:49.004
The jury will hear
this is a couple experimenting

29:49.048 --> 29:52.486
with their sexuality,
jealous of each other.

29:52.529 --> 29:53.835
- Wait, is that necessary?

29:53.879 --> 29:55.010
Haven't they
been through enough?

29:55.054 --> 29:56.925
- Well,
you could always plead guilty.

29:56.969 --> 29:59.101
- Oh, to kidnapping.
I didn't kidnap her.

29:59.145 --> 30:00.842
- We might consider
child endangerment.

30:00.886 --> 30:02.496
- A misdemeanor? Nice try.

30:02.539 --> 30:04.803
- Endangerment, no.
I protected Beth.

30:04.846 --> 30:06.152
- Please.
- Listen.

30:06.195 --> 30:09.982
The DA is never going to agree
to a misdemeanor.

30:10.025 --> 30:12.201
- Okay, guys, we're all
on the same side here.

30:12.245 --> 30:14.160
Don't we all want
what's best for Beth?

30:14.203 --> 30:16.858
- What exactly do you think
that is, Mr. Pearce?

30:16.902 --> 30:18.904
- For the Lees to allow me
to marry her.

30:18.947 --> 30:20.819
- Nick.
- No. Please, go on.

30:20.862 --> 30:22.733
I gotta hear this.

30:22.777 --> 30:24.910
- Okay, I...

30:24.953 --> 30:29.392
I want to protect her
for the rest of her life.

30:29.436 --> 30:31.351
Till death do us part.

30:31.394 --> 30:33.657
If her parents give us
permission to marry,

30:33.701 --> 30:37.139
then none of this has to be
argued in court.

30:37.183 --> 30:39.098
Her parents obviously
have marital problems.

30:39.141 --> 30:43.276
They need time to be together
to heal, to focus on Elijah.

30:43.319 --> 30:44.407
- Look, I'm sorry.

30:44.451 --> 30:46.540
I think I've heard enough.

30:46.583 --> 30:48.194
We are not dropping
the charges.

30:48.237 --> 30:50.370
And I look forward to hearing
your client explain what's best

30:50.413 --> 30:52.067
for Beth on the stand.

30:52.111 --> 30:56.898
♪

30:56.942 --> 30:58.160
- Nick Pearce
won't take a plea?

30:58.204 --> 31:00.293
- No, and his
religious conviction--

31:00.336 --> 31:03.209
I'm starting to think
that it's not an act.

31:03.252 --> 31:04.514
- What does that mean?

31:04.558 --> 31:07.169
- It means he could read
as crazy to the jury.

31:07.213 --> 31:08.344
- So could the family.

31:08.388 --> 31:09.606
- Beth's still not willing
to testify?

31:09.650 --> 31:11.043
- No.
I tried to talk to her parents

31:11.086 --> 31:13.436
about seeing a therapist,
but there's no way

31:13.480 --> 31:14.742
they're gonna go
to an outsider,

31:14.785 --> 31:16.570
so they're having
supper tonight

31:16.613 --> 31:17.745
with their church group.

31:17.788 --> 31:18.920
- Well,
without her cooperation,

31:18.964 --> 31:20.574
I'm gonna need both of you
to testify.

31:20.617 --> 31:21.880
- Copy that, Counselor.

31:21.923 --> 31:24.491
- Well, keep me posted
if anything changes.

31:24.534 --> 31:26.885
- See you tonight?
- You will.

31:29.888 --> 31:33.239
Um, you can go ahead and go.
I'll do the DD5s.

31:33.282 --> 31:35.241
- No, you should go.
You're the one with kids.

31:35.284 --> 31:36.938
- Mm.
- Two little girls, right?

31:36.982 --> 31:38.766
- Jesse and Billie.

31:38.809 --> 31:40.855
- That's--that's a lot
and working full-time.

31:40.899 --> 31:42.944
- I have a lot of help.

31:44.293 --> 31:47.035
- Carisi seems like he's great
with kids.

31:47.079 --> 31:49.429
- Mm-hmm.

31:49.472 --> 31:50.517
Did he tell you that?

31:50.560 --> 31:51.997
- I'm a trained detective.

31:52.040 --> 31:54.695
I kind of, uh, deduced it.

31:54.738 --> 31:57.132
So do he and Captain Murphy
get along?

32:00.005 --> 32:03.051
- Did you deduce that, too,
Detective?

32:03.095 --> 32:05.227
- [laughs]
No, uh,

32:05.271 --> 32:07.577
there's a Hebrew phrase
my dad used to say to me.

32:07.621 --> 32:09.666
[speaking Hebrew]

32:09.710 --> 32:11.277
"You don't choose your family."

32:11.320 --> 32:12.669
- Mm.

32:14.671 --> 32:17.109
Not good. It's the Lees.

32:17.152 --> 32:18.284
Beth is missing.

32:18.327 --> 32:19.720
Again.

32:19.763 --> 32:25.856
♪

32:25.900 --> 32:27.467
- You have to find her.
You have to find her.

32:27.510 --> 32:29.991
- Well, what happened?
- Um, we--we finished supper.

32:30.035 --> 32:31.514
Our Bible study group,
they were loving on her.

32:31.558 --> 32:32.994
She seemed so joyful.

32:33.038 --> 32:35.736
- Okay, and then what?
- Um, uh, they--

32:35.779 --> 32:37.825
she went to the bathroom
inside.

32:37.868 --> 32:39.348
- We've been watching her
like a hawk.

32:39.392 --> 32:40.436
I looked at Claire like

32:40.480 --> 32:41.481
"You should do in there
with her."

32:41.524 --> 32:42.482
- How long ago?

32:42.525 --> 32:44.005
- Uh, a half hour now.

32:44.049 --> 32:45.224
She was only gone ten minutes,
and then Claire went in

32:45.267 --> 32:46.703
to check on her.
- And she was missing?

32:46.747 --> 32:48.183
- Yeah.
- Did anyone see her

32:48.227 --> 32:49.315
inside the restaurant?
- Yeah.

32:49.358 --> 32:50.620
Um, a waitress said

32:50.664 --> 32:52.100
that they saw her leave
out the front door.

32:52.144 --> 32:53.841
- Well, she couldn't
have gone far.

32:53.884 --> 32:54.885
I'll put out an alert.

32:54.929 --> 32:56.844
- This must've been Nick.

32:56.887 --> 32:59.151
We're never gonna
see her again, are we?

32:59.194 --> 33:06.114
♪

33:07.681 --> 33:10.510
- Timestamp says 6:00 p.m.,
and you saw her leave?

33:10.553 --> 33:11.815
- I--I told the parents.

33:11.859 --> 33:14.079
Um, she was in the bathroom
for a while.

33:14.122 --> 33:16.037
I knocked to ask
if she was okay.

33:16.081 --> 33:17.908
- And what'd she say?
- She came right out.

33:17.952 --> 33:19.084
Kinda giddy.

33:19.127 --> 33:21.129
She said she was late
to meet someone.

33:21.173 --> 33:23.088
I told her she looked pretty.

33:23.131 --> 33:24.698
I think she changed
in the bathroom.

33:24.741 --> 33:26.352
- Did she say
where she was going?

33:26.395 --> 33:29.529
- No, no, I had no idea
she was running away.

33:29.572 --> 33:32.053
I--I--I should've told
the parents earlier,

33:32.097 --> 33:34.012
but, you know,
she just seemed so happy--

33:34.055 --> 33:36.884
- You did nothing wrong.
Thank you.

33:36.927 --> 33:38.712
- And Nick somehow got to her.
- Yeah.

33:38.755 --> 33:40.409
- We got a problem.

33:40.453 --> 33:42.411
Molly Adams
from the Lees' church?

33:42.455 --> 33:44.065
- Yeah, we talked to her
and Daniel earlier.

33:44.109 --> 33:45.284
They don't know anything.

33:45.327 --> 33:46.459
- Yeah, well,
she said she didn't wanna

33:46.502 --> 33:47.808
say this around her husband.

33:47.851 --> 33:49.549
- That Beth asked her
to get a message to Nick.

33:49.592 --> 33:50.854
A Bible quote.

33:50.898 --> 33:52.030
- What Bible quote?

33:52.073 --> 33:53.814
- 1 Corinthians 3:11.

33:53.857 --> 33:55.816
"For no one can lay
any other foundation

33:55.859 --> 33:57.513
than that which has been laid."

33:57.557 --> 33:58.775
Molly said it was from Daniel's

33:58.819 --> 34:00.299
"Bridge Over Troubled Water"
sermon.

34:00.342 --> 34:02.170
- White dress
and meeting someone?

34:02.214 --> 34:04.912
- She thinks
that she's getting married.

34:04.955 --> 34:09.090
So somewhere near water
or a bridge.

34:09.134 --> 34:12.267
- She had the Brooklyn Bridge
on her screensaver.

34:12.311 --> 34:17.620
♪

34:17.664 --> 34:19.622
- Nick Pearce!

34:19.666 --> 34:21.624
Step away from the girl.

34:21.668 --> 34:24.149
- What's this about?
- You violated the OOP.

34:24.192 --> 34:26.107
- She asked to see me.
- I did.

34:26.151 --> 34:27.674
Luke and I are exchanging vows.

34:27.717 --> 34:29.545
- Beth, you need to come with--
- Hands behind your back.

34:29.589 --> 34:31.895
- They can't do this to us!
- We need to get you to safety.

34:31.939 --> 34:33.114
- I am safe!

34:33.158 --> 34:34.420
- Okay.
- We're the chosen ones!

34:34.463 --> 34:35.943
- Beth, they're not
gonna believe us.

34:35.986 --> 34:38.424
"We walk by faith,
not by sight."

34:38.467 --> 34:41.949
- You can't hurt us.
I'm carrying God's baby!

34:41.992 --> 34:45.170
[dramatic music]

34:48.608 --> 34:48.782
.

34:48.825 --> 34:50.131
- You can't hurt us.

34:50.175 --> 34:52.133
I'm carrying God's baby!

34:55.658 --> 34:57.704
- What does that mean?
Is she pregnant?

34:57.747 --> 35:00.620
- There's no way to know
if it's true or not.

35:00.663 --> 35:02.361
- Can't you just put Nick
away now?

35:02.404 --> 35:03.536
He's kidnapped her again.

35:03.579 --> 35:05.059
- He violated
the protection order,

35:05.103 --> 35:07.061
but he met Beth
at a public place.

35:07.105 --> 35:08.193
That's not kidnapping.

35:08.236 --> 35:10.499
- And she did initiate
the contact.

35:10.543 --> 35:16.810
- Because of his hold over her.

35:16.853 --> 35:19.204
He was--oh, my God.

35:19.247 --> 35:21.554
He was planning this all along.

35:21.597 --> 35:24.339
Wasn't he?
He was using me and Paul.

35:24.383 --> 35:27.429
Oh, my God.
[sobbing]

35:27.473 --> 35:31.216
- He is obsessed
with your daughter.

35:31.259 --> 35:33.740
And she is with him.

35:33.783 --> 35:35.437
- You're telling me
there's no way

35:35.481 --> 35:37.178
to get him out of her life?

35:38.571 --> 35:40.616
- Your daughter's gonna be 15
next month?

35:44.968 --> 35:46.796
There might be one way.

35:50.104 --> 35:51.584
- Why are we here?

35:51.627 --> 35:54.978
- I know how much
you wanna marry Nick.

35:55.022 --> 35:57.242
Luke. Luke.

35:57.285 --> 36:01.115
And your father and I,
we want you to be happy.

36:01.159 --> 36:03.248
- Then let me see him.

36:03.291 --> 36:05.511
- I'm--I--I'm trying
to figure it out.

36:05.554 --> 36:07.208
There's the Order
of Protection.

36:07.252 --> 36:09.123
- And whose fault is that?

36:09.167 --> 36:13.432
- We--we thought we were doing
the right thing, okay?

36:13.475 --> 36:16.652
Uh, I know now
that we were wrong.

36:16.696 --> 36:23.485
But your dad and I might have
a solution.

36:23.529 --> 36:25.357
- I'm keeping the baby.

36:25.400 --> 36:27.576
And Luke and I,
when I'm old enough,

36:27.620 --> 36:29.361
we're going to get married.

36:29.404 --> 36:32.494
No matter what you say.
- Here's the thing.

36:32.538 --> 36:37.238
You turn 15 in a month.

36:37.282 --> 36:38.805
Don't you?

36:38.848 --> 36:40.546
So if you are pregnant

36:40.589 --> 36:43.636
and if you have
parental consent,

36:43.679 --> 36:47.596
you can get married
in the state of Maryland.

36:47.640 --> 36:50.947
What if we gave permission?

36:50.991 --> 36:52.514
- You'd do that?

36:52.558 --> 36:56.126
You and Dad?
- Beth.

36:56.170 --> 36:58.520
You know, we can't stand
living like this.

36:58.564 --> 37:02.045
You unhappy, hating us.

37:02.089 --> 37:04.918
The state is gonna need proof
of the pregnancy,

37:04.961 --> 37:06.963
proof that Luke is the father.

37:07.007 --> 37:08.182
- I'd need to ask Luke.

37:08.226 --> 37:09.662
- Well, you--you can't.

37:09.705 --> 37:13.013
But, listen,
let's just go to the hospital,

37:13.056 --> 37:14.188
you and I, get this done.

37:14.232 --> 37:16.451
I will--I will tell the ADA

37:16.495 --> 37:18.845
that no one will testify
at trial,

37:18.888 --> 37:23.458
and he'll have
to drop the charges.

37:23.502 --> 37:26.896
- I prayed for this.

37:26.940 --> 37:28.420
- So did I.

37:28.463 --> 37:31.379
[soft music]

37:31.423 --> 37:33.555
♪

37:33.599 --> 37:37.733
Oh, gosh, needed to do this
for a long time.

37:40.780 --> 37:41.955
I love you, Beth.

37:46.264 --> 37:49.441
I love you, Beth.

37:49.484 --> 37:51.443
- Beth's confession
isn't admissible

37:51.486 --> 37:52.966
unless she confirms
with the grand jury.

37:53.009 --> 37:56.491
- But since the fetus' DNA
was a match to Nick Pearce,

37:56.535 --> 37:58.537
that proves Rape Two.

37:58.580 --> 38:00.887
- But Beth won't testify.
- Doesn't matter.

38:00.930 --> 38:03.933
With the DNA, his lawyer's not
gonna let this go to trial.

38:03.977 --> 38:07.589
- [exhales heavily]
Thank you both.

38:07.633 --> 38:10.200
- Does Beth know any of this?

38:10.244 --> 38:12.377
- We're going
to tell her tonight.

38:14.117 --> 38:15.380
- Okay.

38:15.423 --> 38:17.817
Look, I know this has been

38:17.860 --> 38:21.821
an incredibly difficult
decision to make.

38:21.864 --> 38:25.912
- We're going to raise the baby
as our own, and, uh,

38:25.955 --> 38:31.961
work on repairing
our marriage and...

38:32.005 --> 38:35.051
pray that Beth forgives us.

38:35.095 --> 38:37.010
Eventually.

38:37.053 --> 38:39.404
[somber music]

38:39.447 --> 38:41.362
- You'll get through this.

38:41.406 --> 38:45.714
♪

38:45.758 --> 38:47.063
- Okay.

38:47.107 --> 38:48.456
Can you open my present now?

38:48.500 --> 38:50.676
- Of course. I would love to.

38:50.719 --> 38:52.765
[soft sentimental music]

38:52.808 --> 38:55.115
What is this?

38:55.158 --> 39:02.078
♪

39:05.908 --> 39:07.345
- Do you like it?

39:10.870 --> 39:12.393
- I love it.

39:14.961 --> 39:16.266
Come here.

39:16.310 --> 39:23.361
♪

39:29.584 --> 39:31.020
You okay, Mom?

39:32.848 --> 39:34.415
- Yeah, I am.

39:34.459 --> 39:41.596
♪

39:47.994 --> 39:50.953
[dramatic music]

39:50.997 --> 39:57.917
♪

40:18.067 --> 40:21.027
[wolf howls]
